The reproductive system is diaulic (
Fig. 7C
). The preampullary duct widens into the narrow and elongate ampulla. The ampulla bifurcates into the oviduct and the vas deferens. The vas deferens is extremely long and enters the wider proximal portion of the penial sac. The penial papilla is devoid of any armature. The pear-shaped receptaculum seminis joins the oviduct and enters the female gland. The vagina opens ventrally to the penis.
